    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">9:00 AM:</span> Historical Exploration at Plaza Murillo`,
    des: `Begin your La Paz city tour at the iconic stone book statue in Plaza Murillo. Dive into Bolivia's history as you explore the main square and learn about the significance of the surrounding buildings.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">10:00 AM:</span> Traditional Bolivian Breakfast`,
    des: `Visit a local café to enjoy aromatic Bolivian coffee paired with a savory Salteña. Discover why these flavors are staples in Bolivian cuisine.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">11:00 AM:</span> San Pedro Prison and Local Markets`,
    des: `Walk to the infamous San Pedro Prison and hear captivating stories about this unique landmark. Then, immerse yourself in the vibrant colors, sounds, and scents of local markets like Mercado Rodriguez, known for its fresh produce and traditional foods.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">12:30 PM:</span> Journey to Southern La Paz`,
    des: `Experience local life as you travel to the southern part of the city using local transportation. This area is known for its affluence and safety, offering a different perspective of La Paz.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">1:00 PM:</span> Authentic Bolivian Lunch`,
    des: `Savor traditional dishes at a local restaurant, learning about the ingredients and cooking methods that define Bolivian cuisine. Consider including popular dishes such as Lake Titicaca fish or anticuchos.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">2:30 PM:</span> Cable Car Adventure`,
    des: `Ride the Green, Yellow, and Silver cable cars for breathtaking panoramic views of La Paz and El Alto. The cable car system offers a unique perspective of the city and is a must-do activity.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">3:30 PM:</span> Explore El Alto Witch Market`,
    des: `Discover mystical items at the Witch Market in El Alto, learning about Bolivian folklore and traditions. Shop for unique souvenirs to remember your La Paz city tour.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">4:30 PM:</span> Return to La Paz Center`,
    des: `Descend back to the city center via cable car while enjoying more stunning views.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">5:00 PM:</span> Central Witch Market and Shopping Streets`,
    des: `Visit the central Witch Market of La Paz and compare it with El Alto's market. Stroll through popular shopping streets, observing daily life in La Paz.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">6:00 PM:</span> Conclude with Traditional Bolivian Soup`,
    des: `End your culinary journey with a warming bowl of black potato or peanut soup, reflecting on your day of adventures.`
  }],
  included: ["Knowledgeable local guide", "All local transportation", "Coffee and Salteña tasting", "Two traditional meals", "Four scenic cable car rides"],
  exclusion: ["Tips for the guide", "Toilets on the way", "Extra drinks"],
  additionalInformation: ["This immersive 7-hour La Paz city tour promises to awaken your senses and leave you with unforgettable memories. Book now for a day filled with discovery, flavor, and wonder in Bolivia's captivating capital!", '<strong className="font-bold"> Note</strong>:Please make sure you do not book night buses or anything at night since the tour may finish late.', '<strong className="font-bold"> Schedule Variation</strong>:The schedule may vary according to group pace.'],
  faqs: [{
    "question": "What is included in the La Paz city tour?",
