    15: 200
  },
  description: "Experience the stunning landscapes of Salar de Uyuni and beyond on this immersive 3-day tour. From salt flats and colorful lagoons to deserts and geysers, this tour offers an unforgettable journey through Bolivia's most unique natural wonders.",
  tourInfo: ['<strong className="font-bold"> Place Covered</strong>: Uyuni', ' <strong className="font-bold">Duration:</strong> 3 Days, 2 Nights', '<strong className="font-bold">Start Point:</strong> La Paz, Bolivia', '<strong className="font-bold">End Point:</strong>  La Paz, Bolivia', '<strong className="font-bold">Max group size: </strong>  15'],
  highlights: [" •	Visit beautiful Bolivian cities with colonial architecture", "•	Travel to the Uyuni Salt Flats through surreal deserts", "•	Explore marketplaces and get in touch with the locals", "•See Bolivia's main highlights on this amazing 12-day adventure that will leave you awesome memories. Discover La Paz on a city tour, take funny pictures at the famous Uyuni Salt Flats, awe at moon-like landscapes, visit traditional cities like Potosi and Sucre, and learn about the Bolivian way of life."],
  itinerary: [{
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">Day 1:</span> Explore Uyuni, Colchani, and Incahuasi Island`,
    des: `Begin your Salar de Uyuni tour at 10:30 am from Andes 2 Amazon's office. You will first explore Uyuni's famous train graveyard, where Bolivia's first locomotives rest. Next, visit Colchani, a small settlement where you can observe salt miners crafting unique handicrafts and textiles from llama and alpaca fibers. Your journey continues across the stunning Salt Flats of Uyuni, situated at an altitude of 3650 meters. Capture breathtaking photos as you traverse this vast white landscape, visit Los Ojos de Agua Salada, and explore a hotel made entirely of salt that now serves as a museum.After lunch, hike to the top of Isla Incahuasi (Fish Island) to see giant cacti and petrified coral formations. Take creative perspective photos against the salt flats' backdrop. End your day with a beautiful sunset at Pia Pia Island before spending the night in Villa Candelaria at a salt hostel.`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">Day 2:</span> Discover Chiguana Desert and Red Lagoon`,
    des: `Your Salar de Uyuni tour continues with breakfast at 7:00 am before heading to the Chiguana Desert, surrounded by active volcanoes like Ollague. Travel along Pasito Tuntun to witness stunning Andean lagoons inhabited by flamingos. Visit Cañapa Lagoon, Hedionda Lagoon (where you'll have lunch), and Chiarcota Lagoon to observe diverse bird species.Enter Eduardo Avaroa National Reserve to explore the Siloli Desert and photograph the famous 'Rock Tree.' Conclude your day at the Red Lagoon viewpoint to admire its vibrant hue and spot more flamingos.Accommodation`
  }, {
    title: `<span class="me-1 fw-bold">Day 3:</span> Experience Dali Desert and Green Lagoon`,
    des: `Start your day early with breakfast at 5:00 am. Visit Sol de Mañana Geyser to witness fumaroles and boiling mud pots. Relax in open-air hot springs before continuing to the Dali Desert, known for its surreal landscapes that inspired Salvador Dali. Then, visit the Green Lagoon at the foot of Licancabur Volcano near the Bolivia-Chile border. Return to Uyuni via scenic spots like Valley of the Rocks and San Cristobal Village.For those traveling to San Pedro de Atacama in Chile, guides will assist with border crossing arrangements.`
  }],
  included: [" Accommodation: First Day in the Salt hostel LA ESCONDIDA in Villa Candelaria (double rooms).", "Accommodation: Second Day in Basic lodge HUAYLLAJARA with shared facilities", "Pickup from accommodation or bus station", "Transportation in 4WD vehicles", "1 night in a salt hostel, 1 night in shared lodging", "Local driver and English-speaking guide", "Meals: 3 lunches, drinks during meals", "Sleeping bag (if requested)", "Airport pickup"],
  exclusion: ["Entrance fees (Isla Incahuasi, Eduardo Avaroa National Park)", "Toilets on route", "Hot springs entry", "Personal expenses and travel insurance"],
  additionalInformation: ['<strong className="font-bold">Rainy Season: </strong>  January to April, the Salt Flats fill up with water so it is not possible to cross them in the same way as during dry season. As a consequence, the itinerary is modified during that period. The main changes are usually as follow:', "•	Instead of stopping at the Inca Wasy (Fish Island), we stop at a place where the water reflects the sky and where it seems that the sky and the ground merge into one.", "•	On day 1, we might sleep at another location.", "•	We visit the Sol de Mañana Geysers and hot springs at the end of day 2 instead of in the morning of Day 3.", '<strong className="font-bold">Winter Season: (from June to August):</strong> It is not possible to access Eduardo Avaroa national park (red lagoon, dali dessert, green lagoon). However, there is the possibility of visiting black lagoon and rock valley if on the third day of your tour it does not snow. We also may sleep in a different location due to road access.  As it is hard to forecast the weather at high altitudes and due to global warming and it may also snow abruptly. ', '<strong className="font-bold">Temperatures can drop :</strong> It can get very cold especially during the winter months of May to August  so bring extra warm clothes along like a scarf and wool hat to keep warm. We also recommend bringing an extra 5 litres of water so you can have enough water for the whole trip.'],
  suggestedPackingList: ["• Sun hat, sunglasses, sunblock, coat, gloves, wool hat", "• Trekking shoes, warm socks, swimsuit and towel", "• Extra 5 liters of bottled water, snacks, personal medication", "• Flashlight/torch, camera, extra batteries and memory card, charger", "• Hand sanitizer, personal first aid kit"],
  additionalCosts: ['<strong className="font-bold">Extend Your Experience to San Pedro de Atacama:</strong> ', "If you wish to end your tour in San Pedro de Atacama, you can do so for just an additional $15 USD per person. This option provides a comfortable and hassle-free transfer from the Uyuni Salt Flats to this fascinating destination in the Chilean desert. Don’t miss the chance to explore even more breathtaking landscapes!"],
  faqs: [{
    "question": "What should I pack for the Salar de Uyuni tour?",
    "answer": "For your Salar de Uyuni tour, pack essentials like a sun hat, sunglasses, sunblock, a warm coat, gloves, a wool hat, and trekking shoes. Don't forget a swimsuit and towel for the hot springs, extra water (at least 5 liters), snacks, personal medication, a flashlight or torch, a camera with extra batteries and memory card, and a personal first aid kit. The temperatures can drop significantly, especially during the winter months, so bring plenty of warm clothing."
  }, {
    "question": "How does the itinerary change during the rainy season?",
    "answer": "During the rainy season (January to April), the Salt Flats may fill with water, altering the itinerary. Instead of visiting Isla Incahuasi, you'll explore areas where the sky reflects on the water. Accommodation locations might change due to accessibility issues. The visit to Sol de Mañana Geysers and hot springs may also be rescheduled from Day 3 to the end of Day 2."
  }, {
    "question": "Are entrance fees included in the tour price?",
    "answer": "No, entrance fees are not included in the tour price. You will need to pay separately for Isla Incahuasi (30 Bs) and Eduardo Avaroa National Park (150 Bs). Other costs such as toilets on the way (20 Bs) and hot springs entry (6 Bs) are also not included."
  }, {
    "question": "What is the accommodation like during the tour?",
    "answer": "On Day 1, you will stay in a salt hostel in Villa Candelaria with double rooms. On Day 2, accommodation is in a basic lodge with shared facilities at Huayllajara. During certain seasons or weather conditions, accommodations may change due to accessibility issues."
  }, {
    "question": "Is it possible to end the tour in San Pedro de Atacama, Chile?",
    "answer": "Yes, you can choose to end your tour in San Pedro de Atacama instead of returning to Uyuni. Guides will assist with border crossing arrangements on Day 3. However, this transfer must be booked in advance."
  }],
